---

<Layout
	title="Profile"
	description="The official profile page for T L Naparajith, a Software Engineer from India"
>
	<article>
		<h3>Who I am</h3>
		<p>
			I am Naparajith, a Software Development Engineer in Test from India. I am
			passionate about solving coding challenges, simple and complex everyday
			problems and leveraging technology to better the lives of the people
			around me.
		</p>
		<p>
			My career spans software development, engineering, quality assurance, test
			automation, and internal tool development.
		</p>
		<p>
			If you are interested in learning more about my work experience, my
			skills, or the tools I use on a daily basis, you can pruse through the
			pages below:
		</p>

		<div
			class="flex flex-wrap justify-evenly rounded-none border border-border ~gap-2/4 ~p-2/4"
		>
			{
				profile.map((about) => (
					<span>
						<A href={`/profile/${about.id}`}>{about.data.title}</A>
					</span>
				))
			}
		</div>

		<h3>What I do</h3>
		<ol>
			<li>
				Working with Software Businesses
				<ul>
					<li>
						Scaled businesses successfully, emphasizing customer-centric
						decisions
					</li>
					<li>
						Excel in executing ambitious projects and relying on data for
						decisions
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>

			<li>
				Working with Product Teams

				<ul>
					<li>
						Align, contribute to, and grow product teams (10 to 100 people)
					</li>
					<li>
						Fluent in technical and executive languages, crafting narratives for
						inspiration
					</li>
					<li>Significantly contribute to project outcomes</li>
				</ul>
			</li>

			<li>
				Continuous Improvement

				<ul>
					<li>Dedicated to personal and professional growth</li>
					<li>
						Constant learning, omposure in adversity, and high-quality
						decision-making
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>

			<li>
				Networking and Collaboration

				<ul>
					<li>
						Enjoy meeting fellow developers and discussing emerging technologies
					</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
		</ol>

		<h3>More about me</h3>
		<p>
			Many people are curious about my name and what it means. So here is your
			answer.
		</p>
		<p>
			The name Naparajith is deeply rooted in ancient Indian culture and roughly
			translates to <strong>
				<em>
					<u>a person who is undefeated.</u>
				</em>
			</strong>
		</p>
		<p>
			Here is my name translated into a few regional languages, just as a sign
			of my respect for the immense diversity of this wonderful nation.
		</p>
		<table class="caption-top">
			<caption class="mb-4 font-semibold italic">
				Translations in select Indian languages
			</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th>Language</th>
					<th>Name</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tbody>
				{
					translations.map(({ lang, name }) => (
						<tr>
							<td>{lang}</td>
							<td class="font-sans">{name}</td>
						</tr>
					))
				}
			</tbody>
		</table>
		<p>
			Connect for discussions on programming, emerging tech, or software product
			creation. Let's code and innovate together!
		</p>

		<div
			class="flex flex-wrap justify-evenly rounded-none border border-border ~gap-2/4 ~p-2/4"
		>
			{
				links.map((link) => (
					<A href={link.href} title={link.title} target={link.target}>
						{link.innerHTML}
					</A>
				))
			}
		</div>
	</article>
</Layout>
